reviews.text:
Very nice place and coffee.
Only one staff (owner) in the restaurant so it took some time to order and prepare the coffee. Worth the wait! 
We had a wonderful afternoon here.
I love their fresh fruit waffle and vanilla ice cream. A must go every Sunday.

Only coffee shop on Cheung Chau? Power sockets and WiFi so you can work here. Various snacks available made in their toaster oven for $53-63. You can get a couple of these if you want a full meal but they do take 20 mins+ to make. They also sell and send postcards.
A little bit pricey. But the environment is pretty nice. Good for a relaxing afternoon.

Standard coffee shop with decent brews but the staff on duty was being pushy about the orderings, the rules did oblige customers ordering a minimum of one drink and it was explicitly labelled, however i was with a group of 3 and all of them ordered something on the spot. I biologically could not take any drinks so i refused to order yet the staff on duty switched the original open tone to a forceful one. I felt like i was socially pressured into ordering anything by both my peers and the staff. Had to take away at least 1 star from an original 3.5.

Got to try the famous iced pineapples and watermelons when you go there. Really. Can’t miss out the ex-treasure hole of Cheung Po Chai. Did I spell it wrong? ;) Anyway, rent a bike and cycle around the harbour is a fab idea. Enjoy the cool sea breeze on your face while doing that. Got super cool restaurants near the sea, got to try them when you’re around.

Very neat island about an hour’s boat ride from Hong Kong. The islanders are very friendly and the pace of life is much more relaxed on the island. It’s a nice place to get away from the hustle and bustle of Hong Kong

Very nice island to walk around. Lots of Chinese restaurants with very fresh fish. Small alley ways thoughout the island filled with tiny stalls selling nearly everything. Can ride a bike around the whole island in about an hour.
Away from the city. Recommended by my colleagues in Hong Kong. Fresh seafood and a reminder of my hometown Penang.

Amazing Island for a getaway from the city. Only downside is it can get super super super crowed durning the weekend or holiday... as the whole HK is trying to enjoy an island getaway as well.

Food here is lovely, people are nice. filled with hipster places and shops. The beach is always very nice to spend an afternoon. If you are up for adventures, there are few spot you can visit like a cave and small hills and bike around for an alternative experience!
悠閒一天遊✌️

美麗的小島，平日遊客不多，可以休閒地慢慢欣賞風景， 踏單車，游泳。

有海灘，海鮮餐廳，小食店 ，廟宇，海味小店，市集， 渡假屋 ，小酒店。 地方雖小， 但包羅萬有。

係一個好精彩行程。

長洲擁有不少著名的旅遊名勝，其中位於東灣華威酒店旁的長洲石刻更是香港法定古蹟之一[3]。此外島內廟宇亦多不勝數，除規模較大的長洲玉虛宮外，還有四所天后廟，分別是北社天后古廟、南氹天后古廟、大石口天后古廟和西灣天后宮。長洲另外亦有一所洪聖古廟（嘉慶十八年，1813年）、一所水月宮（創建年份不明）和建於1973年的關公忠義亭[7]。每年2月是關公忠義亭的山櫻的開花期，吸引不少人前往欣賞。[42]

其他著名名勝包括前述的張保仔洞和東灣泳灘；以及長洲趣石林、豫章草廬（嘉慶二十一年，1816年）、大石口的義塚（同治十二年，1873年）及摩崖石刻（約20世紀初）、方便醫院（光緒三十二年，1906年）、山頂地界石（1919年）和東南面的小長城等等[7][19]。在西灣長洲碼頭一帶，則布滿海鮮食肆。
